cation";s:3:"alt";s:9:"pinterest";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/09/5a/ed/095aedd03042414ddeeb87d5e2309e86.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcStORrgO2EIgg48aN5lUZ_UoMDBBzwxFC_g1Q";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:1080;s:6:"height";i:1080;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/214695107218902943/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:60:{i:0;s:20:"The show follows Dr.";i:1;s:230:"Ji-Yoon Kim Sandra Oh who navigates her way through a new career peak as she is appointed the chair of the English department which is already dealing with low enrolment issues with a few old and aged faculty who refuse to retire.";i:2;s:187:"Video Source Netflix Netflix YouTube Channel The Chair is a Netflix series created by Amanda Peet and Annie Wyman starring Sandra Oh as the Chair of the English department of her college.";i:3;s:55:"The series is also executive produced by David Benioff.";i:4;s:168:"The longtime professor Joan Hambling Holland Taylor steps in as the new chair when the staff members decide that Ji-Yoon was not dealing with the responsibilities well.";i:5;s:172:"Joan who was absolutely frustrated at the way she has been treated throughout her career compared to her male colleagues takes up the opportunity like a dog with two tails.";i:6;s:119:"The finale leaves the characters with clarity and a sense of limbo as recent events at the University finally conclude.";i:7;s:97:"This recap of Netflixs The Chair season 1 episode 6 the ending explained contains major spoilers.";i:8;s:122:"The Chair sees Sandra Oh at her absolute comedic best in a winning dramedy covering some heavy themes in a compelling way.";i:9;s:32:"Sandra Oh never ceases to amaze.";i:10;s:91:"Most would remember her as the over-zealous security operative Eve Polastri in Killing Eve.";i:11;s:101:"Its no surprise that her next series endeavor on Netflix also looks to have the makings of a winning.";i:12;s:187:"The cor